ZH: 他在事故中受了重伤，现在已经变成了一个残疾人。
EN: He was severely injured in the accident and now he has become disabled.

ZH: 这个组织致力于帮助残疾人融入社会。
EN: This organization is dedicated to helping disabled individuals integrate into society.

ZH: 残疾并不影响他的工作能力。
EN: His disability does not affect his ability to work.

ZH: 她天生残疾，但是依然非常乐观。
EN: She was born with a disability, but she remains very optimistic.

ZH: 这位残疾人士被社会格外尊重。
EN: This disabled person is held in high regard by society.

ZH: 许多残疾人士靠辛勤的劳动维持生计。
EN: Many disabled individuals support themselves through hard work.

ZH: 我们应该尊重每个人，包括残疾人。
EN: We should respect everyone, including those with disabilities.

ZH: 残疾并不意味着无能。
EN: Disability does not mean incapability.

ZH: 他希望能通过自己的努力战胜残疾。
EN: He hopes to overcome his disability through his own efforts.

ZH: 这项政策旨在保障残疾人的权益。
EN: This policy aims to protect the rights of disabled individuals.

ZH: 我们必须为残疾人提供更多的支持和关爱。
EN: We must provide more support and care for disabled individuals.

ZH: 每个人都有权利被平等对待，无论有没有残疾。
EN: Everyone has the right to be treated equally, regardless of disability.

ZH: 他的残疾并没有影响他对生活的热爱。
EN: His disability has not affected his love for life.

ZH: 她是一个残疾人士，但成就却非常了不起。
EN: She is a disabled person, but her achievements are remarkable.

ZH: 我们应该着重培养残疾儿童的自信心。
EN: We should focus on building confidence in children with disabilities.

ZH: 学校应该提供残疾学生所需的支持和资源。
EN: Schools should provide the support and resources needed for disabled students.

ZH: 他正努力适应生活中的一切，尽管拥有残疾。
EN: He is working hard to adapt to everything in life, despite having a disability.

ZH: 他是一名残疾艺术家，作品备受好评。
EN: He is a disabled artist whose works are highly acclaimed.

ZH: 我们应该尽最大努力帮助残疾儿童实现自己的梦想。
EN: We should do our best to help disabled children achieve their dreams.
